1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Embedded Linux?

Simple Definition

Embedded Linux = A customized Linux OS designed to run on dedicated hardware devices.

Unlike laptop Linux, it runs inside:
	‚Ä¢	Switches
	‚Ä¢	Routers
	‚Ä¢	Smart TVs
	‚Ä¢	Cars
	‚Ä¢	Washing machines
	‚Ä¢	IoT sensors

‚∏ª

Real-Life Analogy üì±

Device	OS Type
Laptop	General Linux
Switch	Embedded Linux
Phone firmware	Embedded Linux

Embedded = Built for one specific purpose.

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ Why Use Linux in Embedded Systems?

Because Linux provides:
	‚Ä¢	Hardware driver framework
	‚Ä¢	Networking stack
	‚Ä¢	Filesystems
	‚Ä¢	Security
	‚Ä¢	Open-source flexibility

Vendors customize it for their hardware.

‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ Embedded Linux vs Normal Linux

Feature	Desktop Linux	Embedded Linux
Size	Large	Minimal
GUI	Yes	Usually no
Hardware	Generic	Custom board
Boot time	Slower	Optimized
Storage	GBs	MBs

Switches use headless (no GUI) Linux.

